    # [Scene: Rooftop Nursery & Green Lab | Morning — Years Later]

    scene bg ch15_425c9b_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Bees hum, rain barrels drip intermittently]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, steady piano motif — a minor, repetitive figure]
    "You open your eyes to the smell of wet soil and boiled coffee. The rooftop has grown thicker with life than it did the first season you tended these beds — sedges braided into living walls,"
    "climbing beans choking an old sign that once advertised a developer's promise. Your fingers, still nicked and callused, know the map of these plots by touch: where the beds slope, where the water lingers, which seedlings"
    "will take if you bury them deeper."
    "Rafi moves across the terrace like a linchpin of motion: short, deliberate steps, hands always finding the right place to rest on a shovel or a volunteer's shoulder. He is teaching a circle of teenagers how"
    "to graft sedge stems to a firmer root stock — the living breakwater technique you insisted on when you argued at those early hearings. Their gloves are too big; their faces are earnest."
    show rafi_odeh at left:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "No—no, don't snap it. You cradle it. Think of it like a body, yeah? Gentle, constant pressure. Plants respond to how you touch them."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "I thought I'd be designing seawalls in an office. This is messier. Better, I hope."

    rafi_odeh "You ever think you'd end up teaching kids to stitch the sea shut?"

    maya_corvin "I thought I'd be designing seawalls in an office. This is messier. Better, I hope."

    rafi_odeh "Better for who? Don't make me give a speech about the city."

    maya_corvin "Do it. Your speeches are honest."

    rafi_odeh "My speeches smell like compost. People like that."
    "They laugh, a small burst that breaks the tension. The laughter carries salt on its edges."
    hide rafi_odeh
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch15_425c9b_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A distant tram bell, the squawk of a gull; the rooftop feed chirrups again]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Piano pattern continues, a slightly higher register]
    "You stay long enough to plant three sedge cuttings and to argue one more time about where the next living cofferdam should anchor. Rafi insists on the curve; you want the thicker root mat. You win the argument with a compromise that makes both of you softer around the edges."
    "Before you leave, Lio appears at the stairwell, paint on his knuckles and a new mural sketched over his shoulder. He catches your eye and grins that lopsided grin that used to be defiance and is now a kind of stubborn, weary pride."
    show lio_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lio_corvin "You should see it up close. I kept the colors from the old promenade. The scars better with color, you know?"
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "They do. They take light differently now."

    lio_corvin "Also, I painted a little compass next to one of the cracks. For you."
    "You look at your wrist — the trefoil under your sleeve — and then at the brass compass in your pocket. It is heavy with salt and stories. You run your thumb around it without opening it. The needle is still frozen, but you keep it anyway."

    menu:
        "Demonstrate the grafting with your hands":
            "You roll up your sleeves and guide the youngest kid's hands, feeling the tremor in their fingers translate into something steadier under yours. Rafi nods like you handed him a tool back. || Choice B: 'You unclip a tablet, mark names, and the time slots. Your handwriting on the list is a promise disguised as admin. The kids look at you as if you carried a compass, which in a way you do."
        "Step back and take notes for the rota":

    # --- merge ---
    "You continue tending the nursery and preparing for the day's tasks."
    # [Scene: Market Stalls on Low Row | Midday]
    hide lio_corvin
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch15_425c9b_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Shouts of vendors, the rattle of crates, a sensor pinging tidal updates into a crackly loudspeaker]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A slower cello line underpins the scene]
    "The market feels like an index of what you and the neighborhood have managed to keep: rooftop lettuces spilling into communal pesto, jars labeled with Rafi's handwriting, a stall selling knitted storm scarfs made by neighbors"
    "who lost their roofs but kept their hands. Lio's mural towers at the end of the lane — its colors cycling with new overpaints each season — an annual ledger of memory."
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "You make the best basil in the city, you know. I bribe my colleagues with your pesto whenever I can."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "That's one of the perks of municipal outreach, I suppose."

    elias_kahn "It makes them human. Or at least edible."
    "There is always a pause now, between things said and the truth behind them. You have taught yourself to sit in that pause and not fill it with rhetoric. It keeps you from promising more than is yours to give."

    elias_kahn "How are you, really? The board sessions took... a lot."

    maya_corvin "They took clauses and houses and the patience of a generation. They gave us sensors and a slower mechanism to be heard. Both of those things exist now."

    elias_kahn "Is that—' (he hesitates) '—is that enough for you?"
    "You search his face for the answer you want: the warm amber that used to be unguarded. He gives you a fraction of himself and then draws his hands back to the camera like a person restoring a boundary."

    maya_corvin "Enough is a dangerous word. It's a verb, not a place. I can do a lot with verbs."

    elias_kahn "Good. Because I don't know if I can stop traveling for a while. The mayor's office keeps me running, and I... I don't want to pull you in a direction you won't like."

    maya_corvin "You never pulled me anywhere I didn't already walk toward. Besides, you're here now."

    elias_kahn "For now.' (he exhales) 'I did mean to ask—would you help me document the promenade? The next quarter's report. I want it to say the truth, not the gloss."
    "You and Elias trade a look that holds the weight of the last decade. It is practical and fragile and steadier than either of you have earned."

    menu:
        "Agree to help Elias with the documentation":
            "You nod and accept the camera. Together, you move down the lane, recording the repaired staircases and the places where the living cofferdams have failed. His presence is steady, and you find your hands remembering the language of collaboration. || Choice B: 'You shake your head and name your commitments. Elias takes it like the adult he is, and you both understand that love in this city measures itself in attended meetings and shared debts more than in uninterrupted time."
        "Decline politely—your plate's full with the nursery":

